## Answers to the lab questions:
    answer #a 
    The refactoring phase centralized the styles and modularized the code, making it more maintainable, 
    reusable, and easier to update.

    answer #b
    Export commands allow components and functions to be made available to other parts of the application, 
    enabling code sharing across files.

    answer #c
    The stack in this application manages the navigation between different screens, 
    allowing users to navigate forward and back through a stack of screens (e.g., Home, Details, About).

    The deepest this stack can get is 3 levels deep: Home → Details → About. 
    Each new screen pushes onto the stack, and users can navigate back by popping screens off the stack.

